@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Togglo" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must
have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  The game displays a 7 by 7 tiles board, where each tile has its own
'backing' tile. Any tile can have one of the following colours: red,
green, blue or yellow. If one coloured tile appears on the back, lines
of its colour will be drawn around the edge of the facing tile.
Clicking on a tile will make it pivot, and the facing tile will go to
the back, and the backing tile will become the facing tile.

  The goal of the game is to eliminate all the coloured facing tiles,
by creating horizontal and/or vertical alignments of at least 2
neighbouring tiles that have the same colour. The more there are
neighbouring tiles of the same colour, the more points you will get.

  Note that the backing tiles are there, either to complicate the
game... or help you, if one ore more of these tiles have the same
colour as a facing tile located next to it. However, as long as there
are neighbouring backing tiles of the same colour, the game will
continue.

  Do not isolate tiles of one colour, that is, a tile as well as its
backing tile that have no neighbouring tile of the same colour. If
that happens, the game will let you find the remaining neighbouring
tiles of the same colour, but after that, the game will be over.

  When an alignment of tiles of the same colour have been made, those
tiles are then removed from the board and you get points according to
the number of removed tiles; 2 tiles give 1 point... 5 tiles give 64
points.

  When a board has been cleared, then Togglo will generate a new board
and the game will continue...

  Have fun!

@endnode

